dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4631  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1c. confocal microscopy colocalization with Homer1. \"Subcellular localization of Robo2 in vitro. Ex utero electroporation of Robo2-pHluorin and Homer1 c-tdtomato in pyramidal neurons in vitro. Robo2-pHluorin colocalizes with the excitatory postsynaptic marker Homer1c at the majority of dendritic spines at 14 DIV\"\n\nFigure S1. Supporting figure 1, confocal images of immunofluorescent staining for Robo2, Bassoon and PSD95 in CA1 stratum radiatum at P35. \"High magnification of a putative synapse visualized by direct apposition of Bassoon and PSD95 shows strong enrichment of Robo2 with PSD95 suggesting postsynaptic localization\"\n\nFigure 1d. westernblots show Robo2 localized to pre- and post-synaptic fractions (enriched in the latter).\n\nAnnotated to postsynaptic density based on proximity to the presynapse in imaging data, visualization of plasma membrane-targeted form of ROBO2 (Fig. S1C-E) and interaction with neurexin. Based on the membrane topology of the protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" ontology term was selected.. Experimental description: \"Synaptic fractionation and Western Blotting\nSynaptic fractionation was based on a previously described method (Carlin et al., 1980). Briefly, 20 P21 mice brains were homogenized in 10 mL per 2.5 brains\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4631" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

